Package: datapulse
Version: __VERSION__
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3, python3-gi, python3-gi-cairo, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, gir1.2-appindicator3-0.1, nethogs, iptables, iproute2, policykit-1, libnotify-bin
Conflicts: linuxnetwatch
Replaces: linuxnetwatch
Maintainer: Yousef Algharasi <yousefalgharasi2@gmail.com>
Description: Per-app internet usage monitor and controller
 DataPulse shows how much data each application has downloaded and
 uploaded, filterable by time range, with a tray icon showing live totals.
 It can block an app's network access, throttle its upload bandwidth, and
 auto-block it once it crosses a configured daily data cap.
